From: Yan Zhao <yan.y.zhao@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 8 Jan 2026 15:46:17 -0600
Subject: KVM: SVM: Fix a missing kunmap_local() in sev_gmem_post_populate()
Patch-mainline: v7.0-rc1
Git-commit: 60b590de8b30dad8b11e9e4fba0df2eae81afb98
References: git-fixes

sev_gmem_post_populate() needs to unmap the target vaddr after
copy_from_user() to the vaddr fails.

Fixes: dee5a47cc7a4 ("KVM: SEV: Add KVM_SEV_SNP_LAUNCH_UPDATE command")
Signed-off-by: Yan Zhao <yan.y.zhao@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Michael Roth <michael.roth@amd.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20260108214622.1084057-2-michael.roth@amd.com
Signed-off-by: Sean Christopherson <seanjc@google.com>
Acked-by: Carlos López <clopez@suse.de>
---
 arch/x86/kvm/svm/sev.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/arch/x86/kvm/svm/sev.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kvm/svm/sev.c
@@ -2301,6 +2301,7 @@ static int sev_gmem_post_populate(struct
 			void *vaddr = kmap_local_pfn(pfn + i);
 
 			if (copy_from_user(vaddr, src + i * PAGE_SIZE, PAGE_SIZE)) {
+				kunmap_local(vaddr);
 				ret = -EFAULT;
 				goto err;
 			}
